rComments: She doesn't provide much time in class to appreciate the content, focusing on students scrambling notes onto their pages. Doesn't smile, doesn't say hello or goodbye, and barely makes eye contact. She has in depth knowledge but does not provide sense of appreciation. Tests seem skewed to feminism rather than course or text. Don't need textbook.

She structures her lectures in a clearly, concisely, and creatively. Her tutorials were often very enjoyable, and her lessons on primary source document analysis were more helpful than my historian craft's class. You don't really need the textbook for this class.
Don't take her class if you want an A. Marking is super subjective, reminds me of Essay Writing or something. She is a nice person and everything, I just thinks she marks harder than she should...

Really great professor. As mentioned in other comments, she does not use slides and so attendance to the course is a must but definitely worth it. I learned so much. The textbook was not necessary but helped. She is super nice and is clear about what she is looking for in exams and assignments. Use the office hours if you can! She's very helpful!

great prof, super nice lady. doesn`t give slides or anything though so you really have to go to class and listen/take notes. the book is more of an aide to her lectures. difficulty is alright - not bad
